  "body": "Most listeners don't support listening on unix sockets yet (https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/1605), however the admin listener does.\r\n\r\nOne usability issue with this feature is that if you restart Envoy with the same configuration (including a hot restart) it will fail when it tries to bind to the unix socket. If Envoy calls `unlink()` on the socket just before binding it should fix the problem, although there may an interruption in traffic during a hot restart.\r\n\r\nFor the admin listener this behavior should be okay.\r\n\r\nI might have time this weekend to look at how difficult a PR for this is if there's no opposition to implementing this",
